enumerations.name: DataFilterTypeEnum
enumerations.note: This enum specifies the supported DataFilterTypes. Aggregated by DataFilter.dataFilterType

literals.name: always
literals.description:
No filtering is performed so that the message always passes.
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=0

literals.name: maskedNewDiffersMaskedOld
literals.description:
Pass messages where the masked value has changed. new_value if the new message value is not filtered out)
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=1

literals.name: maskedNewDiffersX
literals.description:
Pass messages whose masked value is not equal to a specific value x
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=2

literals.name: maskedNewEqualsX
literals.description:
Pass messages whose masked value is equal to a specific value x
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=3

literals.name: never
literals.description:
The filter removes all messages.
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=4

literals.name: newIsOutside
literals.description:
Pass a message if its value is outside a predefined boundary.
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=5

literals.name: newIsWithinmin
literals.description:
Pass a message if its value is within a predefined boundary.
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=6

literals.name: oneEveryN
literals.description:
Pass a message once every N message occurrences. Each time the message is received or transmitted, occurrence is incremented by 1 after filtering. Length of occurrence is 8 bit (minimum).
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=7
